sample.title: How To 'Invest‚Äô In Private Companies Like OpenAI And SpaceX
sample.description:
Private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX have captured enormous investor enthusiasm in recent years, driving up their valuations. Yet because they‚Äôre privately held, they‚Äôve remained largely inaccessible to ordinary investors. Now a new approached called tokenization could change that by giving retail investors access to investments aligned with the performance of private companies. But despite its appeal, some worry that tokenizing private companies could be a way to bypass longstanding regulations meant to protect investors.

Putin made his comments during a joint media briefing with India‚Äôs Prime Minister Narendra Modi, while on his visit to India.

sample.title: Eurovision boycott over Israel participation | BBC News
sample.description:
Ireland, Spain, the Netherlands and Slovenia will boycott the 2026 Eurovision Song Contest, after it was decided that Israel could compete.
 
They were among a number of countries who called for Israel to be excluded over the war in Gaza and accusations of unfair voting practices.
 
Ireland's RT√â said it felt that its "participation remains unconscionable given the appalling loss of lives in Gaza and the humanitarian crisis there which continues to put the lives of so many civilians at risk."
 
However, at a meeting in Geneva where a vote was held on new safeguards, a "large majority" of members agreed there was no need for a further vote on Israel‚Äôs participation and that Eurovision 2026 could proceed as planned, the European Broadcasting Union (EBU) said.
 
The BBC, which broadcasts Eurovision in the UK, said in a statement: "We support the collective decision made by members of the EBU. This is about enforcing the rules of the EBU and being inclusive."
